#: ../../library/exceptions.rst:63
msgid "raise new_exc from original_exc"
msgstr "raise new_exc from original_exc"

#: ../../library/exceptions.rst:65
msgid ""
"The expression following :keyword:`from<raise>` must be an exception or "
"``None``. It will be set as :attr:`!__cause__` on the raised exception. "
"Setting :attr:`!__cause__` also implicitly sets the :attr:`!"
"__suppress_context__` attribute to ``True``, so that using ``raise new_exc "
"from None`` effectively replaces the old exception with the new one for "
"display purposes (e.g. converting :exc:`KeyError` to :exc:`AttributeError`), "
"while leaving the old exception available in :attr:`!__context__` for "
"introspection when debugging."
msgstr ""
"A expressĂŁo a seguir :keyword:`from<raise>` deve ser uma exceĂ§ĂŁo ou "
"``None``. Ela serĂˇ definida como :attr:`!__cause__` na exceĂ§ĂŁo levantada. A "
"definiĂ§ĂŁo de :attr:`!__cause__` tambĂ©m define implicitamente o atributo :"
"attr:`!__suppress_context__` como ``True``, de modo que o uso de ``raise "
"new_exc from None`` substitui efetivamente a exceĂ§ĂŁo antiga pela nova para "
"fins de exibiĂ§ĂŁo (por exemplo, convertendo :exc:`KeyError` para :exc:"
"`AttributeError`), deixando a exceĂ§ĂŁo antiga disponĂ­vel em :attr:`!"
"__context__` para introspecĂ§ĂŁo durante a depuraĂ§ĂŁo."

#: ../../library/exceptions.rst:74
msgid ""
"The default traceback display code shows these chained exceptions in "
"addition to the traceback for the exception itself. An explicitly chained "
"exception in :attr:`!__cause__` is always shown when present. An implicitly "
"chained exception in :attr:`!__context__` is shown only if :attr:`!"
"__cause__` is :const:`None` and :attr:`!__suppress_context__` is false."
msgstr ""
"O cĂłdigo de exibiĂ§ĂŁo padrĂŁo do traceback mostra essas exceĂ§Ăµes encadeadas, "
"alĂ©m do traceback da prĂłpria exceĂ§ĂŁo. Uma exceĂ§ĂŁo explicitamente encadeada "
"em :attr:`!__cause__` sempre Ă© mostrada quando presente. Uma exceĂ§ĂŁo "
"implicitamente encadeada em :attr:`!__context__` Ă© mostrada apenas se :attr:"
"`!__cause__` for :const:`None` e :attr:`!__suppress_context__` for falso."

#: ../../library/exceptions.rst:80
msgid ""
"In either case, the exception itself is always shown after any chained "
"exceptions so that the final line of the traceback always shows the last "
"exception that was raised."
msgstr ""
"Em qualquer um dos casos, a exceĂ§ĂŁo em si sempre Ă© mostrada apĂłs todas as "
"exceĂ§Ăµes encadeadas, de modo que a linha final do traceback sempre mostre a "
"Ăşltima exceĂ§ĂŁo que foi levantada."

#: ../../library/exceptions.rst:86
msgid "Inheriting from built-in exceptions"
msgstr "Herdando de exceĂ§Ăµes embutidas"

#: ../../library/exceptions.rst:88
msgid ""
"User code can create subclasses that inherit from an exception type. It's "
"recommended to only subclass one exception type at a time to avoid any "
"possible conflicts between how the bases handle the ``args`` attribute, as "
"well as due to possible memory layout incompatibilities."
msgstr ""
"O cĂłdigo do usuĂˇrio pode criar subclasses que herdam de um tipo de exceĂ§ĂŁo. "
"Ă‰ recomendado criar subclasse de apenas um tipo de exceĂ§ĂŁo por vez para "
"evitar possĂ­veis conflitos entre como as bases tratam o atributo ``args``, "
"bem como devido a possĂ­veis incompatibilidades de layout de memĂłria."

#: ../../library/exceptions.rst:95
msgid ""
"Most built-in exceptions are implemented in C for efficiency, see: :source:"
"`Objects/exceptions.c`.  Some have custom memory layouts which makes it "
"impossible to create a subclass that inherits from multiple exception types. "
"The memory layout of a type is an implementation detail and might change "
"between Python versions, leading to new conflicts in the future.  Therefore, "
"it's recommended to avoid subclassing multiple exception types altogether."
msgstr ""
"A maioria das exceĂ§Ăµes embutidas sĂŁo implementadas em C para eficiĂŞncia, "
"veja: :source:`Objects/exceptions.c`. Algumas tĂŞm layouts de memĂłria "
"personalizados, o que impossibilita a criaĂ§ĂŁo de uma subclasse que herda de "
"vĂˇrios tipos de exceĂ§ĂŁo. O layout de memĂłria de um tipo Ă© um detalhe de "
"implementaĂ§ĂŁo e pode mudar entre as versĂµes do Python, levando a novos "
"conflitos no futuro. Portanto, Ă© recomendĂˇvel evitar criar subclasses de "
"vĂˇrios tipos de exceĂ§ĂŁo."

